---
title: "Figure 5.4: Sequence Diagram — User Registration with OTP Email Verification"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant B as Browser
    participant PH as PortalRequestHandler
    participant DB as Database
    participant SMTP as Gmail SMTP

    B->>PH: GET /register
    PH-->>B: Render register.html

    B->>PH: POST /register (full_name, email, password, school, phone)
    PH->>DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?
    DB-->>PH: No existing user

    PH->>PH: hash_password(password) → SHA-256 digest
    PH->>DB: INSERT INTO users (full_name, email, password, role, is_verified=0)
    DB-->>PH: user_id

    PH->>PH: generate_otp() → 6-digit OTP
    PH->>DB: INSERT INTO verification_tokens (token, user_id, expires_at = now+600)
    DB-->>PH: OK

    PH->>SMTP: send_otp_email(email, otp) via smtplib.SMTP_SSL port 465
    SMTP-->>PH: Email sent

    PH-->>B: Redirect to /verify-otp

    B->>PH: POST /verify-otp (otp_code)
    PH->>DB: SELECT * FROM verification_tokens WHERE token = ? AND expires_at > now()
    DB-->>PH: Valid token record

    PH->>DB: UPDATE users SET is_verified = 1 WHERE id = user_id
    PH->>DB: DELETE FROM verification_tokens WHERE token = ?
    DB-->>PH: OK

    PH-->>B: Redirect to /login
